Q: Converting an UTF-16 index to a UTF-8 compatible one A: <p>Old question, but it came up in my feed.  You want to store the raw utf-16 bytes returned by this API, after any endian-conversion necessary, in a <code>Vec[u16]</code>.  Extract the substring you want from this entity by turning the provided offset and length into a <code>&amp;[u16]</code> array slice, perhaps with code like:</p>
<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>let start_index_utf16 = entity.offset as usize;
let end_index_utf16 = start_offset + entity.length as usize;
let substring: &amp;[u16] = &amp;utf16_str[start_offset..end_offset];
</code></pre>
<p>You can then pass the slice to <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/string/struct.String.html#method.from_utf16" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><code>String::from_utf16</code></a>  to convert to UTF-8.</p>

